den","1138–Female":"1138–Overleden","1150–Female":"1150–Overleden","1170–1245":"1170–1245","1265–Male":"1265–Overleden","1215–Male":"1215–Overleden","1205–Female":"1205–Overleden","aproximadamente 1150":"circa 1150","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","aproximadamente 1135":"circa 1135","1305":"1305","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1235":"1235","1245":"1245","1135":"1135","1265":"1265","Saavedra, Begonte, Lugo, Galicia, Spain":"Saavedra, Begonte, Lugo, Galicia, Spanje","Galicia, Espanha":"Galicia, Spanje","Portugal":"Portugal"},"en":{"aproximadamente 1135–":"about 1135–Deceased","1135–Male":"1135–Deceased","1250–1305":"1250–1305","–Female":"Deceased","1138–Female":"1138–Deceased","1150–Female":"1150–Deceased","1170–1245":"1170–1245","1265–Male":"1265–Deceased","1215–Male":"1215–Deceased","1205–Female":"1205–Deceased","aproximadamente 1150":"about 1150","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","aproximadamente 1135":"about 1135","1305":"1305","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1235":"1235","1245":"1245","1135":"1135","1265":"1265","Saavedra, Begonte, Lugo, Galicia, Spain":"Saavedra, Begonte, Lugo, Galicia, Spain","Galicia, Espanha":"Galicia, Spain","Portugal":"Portugal","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fernandes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Manuel, Jose, Carlos, Luis, Fernando, Jorge, Mario, Francisco, Orlando, Ana, Abilio, Americo.  Portuguese Joao, Joaquim, Henrique, Ilidio, Paulo, Agostinho, Amadeu, Manoel, Aderito, Lourenco, Marcio, Serafim.","Portuguese and Galician: patronymic from the personal name   Fernando  . This is one of the most common surnames in Portugal. It is also found in Goa and elsewhere on the west coast of India, having been taken there by Portuguese colonists.","Spanish: variant or altered form of <b>Fernández</b> (see   Fernandez  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Fernando","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Manuel, Luis, Orlando, Aida, Carlos, Jesusa, Rodolfo, Ruben, Adela, Alfredo, Alicia.  Indian Rohan, Lalith, Nimal, Rajiv, Sanjeeva, Shanthi, Anil, Anusha, Dushan, Kapila, Lakshman, Mallika.","Spanish and Portuguese: from the personal name <i>Fernando</i>, a younger form of <i>Ferdinando</i> (see   Ferdinand  ). This surname is also found in southern Italy, mainly in Naples and Palermo, since the period of Spanish dominance there, and as a result of the expulsion of the Jews from Spain and Portugal at the end of the 15th century, many of whom moved to Italy. It is also common in western India and especially in Sri Lanka, where it was taken by Portuguese colonists in the 16th century."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Lima","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Manuel, Carlos, Mario, Luis, Juan, Raul, Ricardo, Roberto, Eduardo, Francisco, Pedro.  Portuguese Joao, Paulo, Duarte, Guilherme, Vasco, Joaquim, Albano, Catarina, Goncalo, Margarida, Terezinha.","Spanish: possibly from <i>lima</i> ‘file’.","Portuguese: topographic name for someone living on the banks of the river of this name (of pre-Roman origin, probably akin to a Celtic element <i>lemos</i>, <i>limos</i> ‘elm’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Limas","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Jesus, Manuel, Juan, Lupe, Raul, Ricardo, Ruben, Fernando, Francisco, Luis, Maria Del Rosario.","Portuguese and Spanish: variant of   Lima  ."]}]},{"name":"Fernão","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: habitational name from any of various places called Fernau, Fernow, or Viernau."],"variants":[{"name":"Fearnow","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Fernau   or of <b>Virnau</b> (also <b>Viernow</b>), a habitational name from Viernau in Thuringia."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Fernão Fernandes de Lima was born about 1135, in Portugal, his father, Fernão Anes De Lima, was -79 and his mother, Teresa Anes de Maia, was -68. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Sancha Vasques de Soverosa."},"et":{"aproximadamente 1135–":"umbes 1135–Surnud","1135–Male":"1135–Surnud","1250–1305":"1250–1305","–Female":"Surnud","1138–Female":"1138–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1170–1245":"1170–1245","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","aproximadamente 1150":"umbes 1150","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","aproximadamente 1135":"umbes 1135","1305":"1305","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1235":"1235","1245":"1245","1135":"1135","1265":"1265","Saavedra, Begonte, Lugo, Galicia, Spain":"Saavedra, Begonte, Lugo, Galicia, Hispaania","Galicia, Espanha":"Galicia, Hispaania","Portugal":"Portugal"},"fi":{"aproximadamente 1135–":"noin 1135–Kuollut","1135–Male":"1135–Kuollut","1250–1305":"1250–1305","–Female":"Kuollut","1138–Female":"1138–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1170–1245":"1170–1245","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1215–Male":"1215–Kuollut","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","aproximadamente 1150":"noin 1150","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","aproximadamente 1135":"noin 1135","1305":"1305","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1138":"1138","1235":"1235","1245":"1245",